The paper proposes a new neural policy architecture for multi-agent reinforcement learning, which involves learning multi-agent relationships at the policy level via an attentional architecture. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), robotics (cs.RO), and systems and control (cs.SY).
